# @param {Integer[][]} grid
# @return {Integer[]}
def good_subsetof_binary_matrix(grid)
  m, n = grid.size, grid[0].size
  best_subset = []

  # Iterate through all possible subsets of rows
  (1..m).each do |subset_size|
    (0...m).to_a.combination(subset_size).each do |subset|
      # Check if current subset is a good subset
      is_good_subset = true
      (0...n).each do |col|
        col_sum = subset.sum { |row| grid[row][col] }
        if col_sum > subset_size / 2
          is_good_subset = false
          break
        end
      end

      if is_good_subset
        # If a good subset is found with a size larger than any previously found, update best_subset
        if subset.size > best_subset.size
          best_subset = subset
          break # Break early since we prefer the first valid subset found
        end
      end
    end
    break unless best_subset.empty? # Stop if we've found a good subset
  end

  best_subset
end
